4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, termination dates are
6 established for enumerated state agencies. The agencies
7 are periodically reviewed by the Alabama Sunset
8 Committee. After the review process is completed, the
9 committee prepares its recommendation for the agencies
10 to the Legislature in the form of sunset bills which
11 either continue, terminate, or continue with
12 modification each agency reviewed.
13 This bill would provide for the continuance of
14 the Alabama Construction Recruitment Institute until
15 October 1, 2030, with the following changes: To remove
16 the institute's authority to own property and to employ
17 an executive director or other professionals; to place
18 the institute as a division within the Alabama
19 Department of Workforce; to require the department to
20 provide all necessary administrative services for the
21 institute; to authorize the Secretary of Workforce to
22 provide for an executive director and outside experts
23 for the institute; and to transfer all property of the
24 institute to the department.
25
26
27 A BILL
28 TO BE ENTITLED
Page 1

TO BE ENTITLED
SB103 INTRODUCED
29 AN ACT
30
31 Relating to the Alabama Sunset Law; to continue the
32 existence and functioning of the Alabama Construction
33 Recruitment Institute until October 1, 2030, with certain
34 modifications; to amend Section 41-10-725, Code of Alabama
35 1975, to remove the institute's authority to own property and
36 to employ an executive director or other professionals; and to
37 add Section 41-10-723.1 to the Code of Alabama 1975, to place
38 the institute as a division within the Alabama Department of
39 Workforce; to require the department to provide all necessary
40 administrative services for the institute; to authorize the
41 Secretary of Workforce to provide for an executive director
42 and outside experts for the institute; and to transfer all
43 property of the institute to the department.
44 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
45 Section 1. Pursuant to the Alabama Sunset Law, the
46 Sunset Committee recommends the continuance of the Alabama
47 Construction Recruitment Institute until October 1, 2030, with
48 additional recommendation for statutory change as set out in
49 Section 3.
50 Section 2. The existence and functioning of the
51 Alabama Construction Recruitment Institute, created and
52 functioning pursuant to Sections 41-10-720 to 41-10-732,
53 inclusive, Code of Alabama 1975, is continued until October 1
54 2030, and those code sections are expressly preserved.
55 Section 3. Section 41-10-725, Code of Alabama 1975, is
56 amended to read as follows:
