150 Section 4. Section 41-10-723.1 is added to the Code of
151 Alabama 1975, to read as follows:
152 §41-10-723.1
153 (a) Beginning on October 1, 2026, the institute is a
154 division within the Alabama Department of Workforce.
155 (b) The department shall provide all administrative
156 services necessary for the institute to carry out its duties
157 and powers pursuant to this article including:
158 (1) Financial services;
159 (2) Legal services;
160 (3) Dedicated office space;
161 (4) Administrative staff, who are shared with or solely
162 dedicated to the institute, and other personnel as necessary
163 for the efficient operation of the institute;
164 (5) Information technology services, including website
165 maintenance and dedicated phone lines and email addresses for
166 institute members and staff; and
167 (6) Necessary office furniture and supplies.
168 (c) Any contract or binding agreement for
Page 6

(c) Any contract or binding agreement for
SB103 INTRODUCED
169 administrative services executed by the institute before June
170 1, 2026, shall continue in effect until expiration as provided
171 by its terms. After expiration, the department shall assume
172 all administrative services provided by subsection (b).
173 (d)(1) Commencing on October 1, 2026, the Secretary of
174 Workforce, upon the recommendation of the institute, may
175 employ an individual to serve as the executive director of the
176 institute using funds appropriated for use by the institute.
177 (2) When necessary, the department may retain the
178 services of outside experts, including accountants, attorneys,
179 engineers, and consultants using funds appropriated for use by
180 the institute on behalf of the institute.
181 (e) On October 1, 2026, all real and personal property
182 and all other effects of the institute shall transfer to the
183 department.
184 Section 5. The Legislature concurs in the
185 recommendations of the Sunset Committee as provided in
186 Sections 1, 2, 3, and 4.
187 Section 6. This act shall become effective June 1,
188 2026.
